On Mon, 22 Feb 2010, Heather Woltz wrote:
> I can drive the bus for about 10 or so miles, pulling the pedal up each
> time i use the brakes to fully release them, then wheels and brakes start to
> heat up and drag a lot
>
> Any more suggestions?

couple shots in the dark...

. is the vaccuum line from the engine to the boster connected.
. no leaks.
. is the one way valve in the vaccuum line turned right way round. is easy 
to get reversed.

. is the spring on the pedal lever working correctly
Bentley Section 8, Chapter 12, page 34, fig 12.1  part #16

. is the pivots on the brake lever rod free or sticking

> Anyone in portland that has a known good one that they would like to sell?

far from Portland so no, sorry

